<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROONEY REDUX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Andrew Christie (Letters, March 3) criticizes Howard Rosenberg by asserting the 
columnist "protests the inevitable reaction to his defense of (Andy) Rooney by 
saying, gee, if you criticize a black person these days everybody calls you a 
racist. 
</P>
<P>
That's disingenuous. And arrogant. And dumb." 
</P>
<P>
Christie failed to include the most important point: And true. 
</P>
<P>
LANNY R. MIDDINGS, San Ramon 
