<HEADLINE>
<P>
COVERAGE OF GATHERS' DEATH BRINGS STRONG REACTION FROM READERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After sifting through countless stories about athletes on drugs, lockouts, 
point shaving and the like, it was always a pleasure to flip to the South Bay 
section of The Times and find a story about Hank Gathers and the Loyola Lions. 
I was looking forward to the day when news about Loyola would supplant that 
about USC, UCLA and even the Lakers on the front page of the sports section. 
</P>
<P>
It happened on Monday, but not at all in the way it was supposed to. 
</P>
<P>
KEN KRUG, Redondo Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
