<HEADLINE>
<P>
IT MAKES MORE SENSE TO MAKE MORE DOLLARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I couldn't believe what I was reading. Brian Weston (Viewpoint, March 3) wants 
to get rid of Curtis Crayon, who has picked winners paying $253 more than Bob 
Mieszerski, and replace him with "someone who knows what he is doing." 
</P>
<P>
Then he calls Mieszerski's picks "rock-solid and professional." A person goes 
to the track to make as much money as he can, not to see how many winners he 
can pick. 
</P>
<P>
WALTER HARRIS, Woodland Hills 
</P>
