<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROBERT RUSSELL JACQUET; TRUMPET PLAYER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robert Russell Jacquet, 72, a trumpet player and singer, and brother of jazz 
saxophonist Illinois Jacquet. He had played regularly with his brother's band 
since 1944 and briefly led his own group at the old Cotton Club in Hollywood. 
He also led jazz groups in San Diego and other Southland locales and later 
moved to Oakland before returning to Los Angeles, where he died Feb. 28 of a 
heart attack. 
</P>
