<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAMS SIGN PLAN B GUARD MILINICHIK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rams announced the signing of six free agents Friday, including Plan B 
guard Joe Milinichik of the Detroit Lions. 
</P>
<P>
Milinichik, 6-feet-5, 275 pounds, played in all 16 games for Detroit last 
season, starting once. 
</P>
<P>
He was a four-year starter at North Carolina State and the Lions' third-round 
draft choice in 1986. Milinichik, who will turn 27 March 30, spent his entire 
rookie season on injured reserve after suffering a dislocated elbow. 
</P>
<P>
After being injured during training camp in 1989, Milinichik lost his starting 
job to rookie Mike Utley. 
</P>
<P>
With the Rams, Milinichik fills a void left by guard/center Tony Slaton, a Plan 
B free agent who signed last week with Dallas. 
</P>
<P>
In lesser moves, the team signed tight end Richard Ashe and wide receiver 
Anthony Sargent, both of whom finished the 1989 season on the team's 
developmental squad. 
</P>
<P>
Others signed included guard Jeff Mickel, Eastern Washington; cornerback Mario 
Mitchell, San Diego State, and wide receiver Derrick Saison, Howard University. 
CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</TEXT>
