<HEADLINE>
<P>
ONE TICKET WITH 8 WINNERS PAYS $494,252 IN PICK NINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A single Pick Nine ticket at Santa Anita Friday had eight of the day's nine 
winning horses on it, and that ticket was worth $494,252.40. 
</P>
<P>
There was a mandatory payout in the Pick Nine, after the carryover pool reached 
$525,915 at the end of Thursday's program. 
</P>
<P>
Under Pick Nine rules, the payout is made on the day after the carryover 
exceeds $500,000. 
</P>
<P>
Friday's crowd of 27,972, including 20,260 at the track, wagered another 
$538,240 for a chance at a big payoff. A single ticket with all nine winning 
horses would have been worth nearly $1 million. 
</P>
<P>
With no perfect tickets, there was a three-tiered payoff. In addition to the 
single winner with eight correct picks, 36 tickets with seven were worth 
$2,941.80 each, and 563 with six returned $188 apiece. 
</P>
</TEXT>
