</P>
<P>
DONNELLY LEADS FOOTHILL WITH HIS BAT AND ARM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kent Donnelly led Foothill High School to a 15-2 victory over Tustin in a 
championship semifinal of the Newport-Tustin baseball tournament Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Donnelly hit a two-run home run in the third inning to give Foothill a 3-2 
lead. Donnelly also pitched five innings and struck out seven. 
</P>
<P>
Foothill will play Mater Dei in the final at 2 p.m. today at Tustin High 
School. 
</P>
<P>
In the other championship semifinal, Lionel Hastings had two hits and three 
RBIs to lead Mater Dei to a 4-1 victory. Hastings' bases-loaded single in the 
fourth scored two runs. 
</P>
<P>
Sean Sutton (1-1) went five innings, allowed both hits, struck out four, walked 
four and allowed Mission Viejo's unearned run. Hastings relieved him, retiring 
all six batters he faced. 
</P>
<P>
In the consolation semifinals: 
</P>
<P>
Estancia 15, Newport Harbor 5 -- Ruben Mora went four for four, had two 
doubles, a home run, scored three runs and had six RBIs to lead Estancia (2-1). 
Mora led Estancia's 11-run, eight-hit second inning by hitting an RBI double 
and a three-run home run. Newport Harbor is 2-2. Also for Estancia, Dan Ucker 
had two hits and three RBIs and Greg Brannis got his first victory. 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley 7, Esperanza 6 (8 innings) -- John Mackay hit a home run in 
the bottom of the eighth inning for Capistrano Valley (3-2) at Corona del Mar. 
The Cougars scored the tying run in the seventh when Tony Solliday scored from 
second on an error. Solliday hit a two run home run in the fourth inning. 
</P>
<P>
In other Newport-Tustin tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 2, Santa Ana Valley 0 -- Ramiro Gracia singled, tripled, scored and 
had an RBI to lead Saddleback (4-1) at Foothill. 
</P>
<P>
Orange 3, Corona del Mar 1 -- Trailing 1-0, host Orange rallied to win a 
consolation game with a run in the third on a sacrifice fly by Jason Smith and 
two in the fourth on a double by Chris Thompson. 
</P>
<P>
Josh Belovsky (1-0) allowed a run on two hits in five innings for Orange (1-4). 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 7, Costa Mesa 3 -- Jesse Rosas (2-0) struck out six in four innings 
and David Fausto struck out six in three innings of relief for Santa Ana in a 
consolation game. Rosas had two hits, including a triple, drove in a run and 
scored a run. Santa Ana is 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
In the El Segundo baseball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Westminster 5, South Torrance 3 -- Mark Murphy (1-0) allowed four hits and no 
earned runs in a consolation semifinal. Dennis Barclay had two hits and an RBI 
for Westminster (2-2), which scored four runs in the third inning on a walk, 
three consecutive singles and an error. 
</P>
<P>
Gahr 3, Brea-Olinda 2 -- Host Gahr scored three runs in the first inning and 
Brea-Olinda scored one in each of the first two innings in a consolation game. 
</P>
<P>
In the Oceanside baseball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
