<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
GOODCASE KEEPS UC IRVINE ROLLING WITH 9-2 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UC Irvine won its 11th game in its last 13 by defeating UC Riverside, 9-2, in a 
nonconference baseball game at UC Irvine Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Goodcase led the Anteaters with a three-run home run in the third inning 
to give Irvine a 3-0 lead. Goodcase had three hits and five runs batted in. 
</P>
<P>
Osmar DeChavez went four for four and scored three runs for Irvine (14-8). Ken 
Whitworth (6-1) pitched his third consecutive complete game, allowing 11 hits, 
two runs and striking out four. 
</P>
<P>
In other nonconference baseball games: 
</P>
<P>
U.S. International 3, Cal State Fullerton 2 (10 innings) -- Bruce Moutaw had an 
unassisted triple play in the first inning and Kyle Sebach hit a solo home run 
in the 10th inning to lead host USIU (6-12-1). Rich Gonzales had two hits, 
including a home run, and Steve Sisko had two hits for Cal State Fullerton 
(8-7). USIU only had four hits -- two home runs and two doubles. 
</P>
<P>
In California Collegiate Athletic Assn. men's baseball: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 10, Cal Poly Pomona 2 -- Jody Garcia hit a two-run home run, his fourth 
of the season, to give Chapman a 3-0 first-inning lead at Hart Park in Orange. 
Mike Kelly had two hits, two runs and two RBIs, and Jason Rolish had two hits, 
two runs and an RBI for Chapman (10-9, 2-4). 
</P>
