<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oscar Mayer to Shut Vernon Plant: Lunch meat giant Oscar Mayer Foods Corp. will 
close its Vernon processing plant at the end of September, laying off 537 
workers, company officials said. The company, which purchased the plant in 
1951, blamed the closure on high operating costs. Based in Madison, Wis., Oscar 
Mayer operates 21 manufacturing plants nationwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
