<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHOOTING SUSPECT JAILED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A San Diego man was arrested early Friday morning at a La Mesa nightclub in 
connection with the shooting of a Camp Pendleton-based Marine at the club, La 
Mesa police reported. 
</P>
<P>
Christopher Avalon Miller, 23, is being held without bail in County Jail on 
suspicion of attempted murder. 
</P>
<P>
Miller allegedly shot Steven Christian in the arm and leg during an argument 
Feb. 4 in the parking lot of Cafe Vid in the 7300 block of El Cajon Boulevard, 
Sgt. Charles Peightal said. 
</P>
<P>
Peightal said Miller was identified by bouncers at the club and was arrested at 
1 a.m. Friday as he left. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
