<HEADLINE>
<P>
26-SQUARE-MILE AREA SPRAYED FOR MEDFLIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aerial spraying against the Medfly took place as scheduled Friday night over 
portions of Brea, Fullerton and La Habra, as well as adjacent parts of Los 
Angeles County, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The spraying had been postponed from earlier in the week when high winds 
grounded helicopters. 
</P>
<P>
Friday's was the fifth spraying of the 26-square-mile target area. State 
officials say the area will probably be sprayed 10 to 12 times, and as 
frequently as once a week during summer. 
</P>
<P>
The next spraying is scheduled for March 26. 
</P>
<P>
Information on spraying is available by calling (714) 447-7118. 
</P>
</TEXT>
